    "prompt": "<div>\n<div class=\"stimulus_reference\">\n<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure presents two circular disks on a horizontal surface. A cylinder shown as a dashed line is inside the larger disk. Point P on the outer disk is indicated in the middle of the horizontal surface, directly below the center of the disks. An arrow labeled “d” originates from the right side of the cylinder upward about 45 degrees toward the top right side of the figure, and if extended in the other direction, it would intersect Point P. A leftward arrow labeled “b” extends from the cylinder, and a rightward pointing arrow labeled “a” extends to the right of the cylinder. An upward pointing arrow labeled c extends from the cylinder.\" height=\"174\" src=\"/images/b220b9b4bcac5fdf404866234613c78a.png\" width=\"207\"></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A spool is made of two circular disks connected to the ends of a cylinder so that the centers of the disks and the cylinder are aligned. In the figure above, the cylinder is shown as the dashed circle, and the disk on one end of the cylinder is shown as the larger solid circle. The spool is at rest on a level horizontal surface. A string attached to the cylinder is pulled gently so that the spool can rotate without slipping on the surface at point P. A force <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"F\"><math alttext=\"F\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>F</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> is pulled in the direction of arrow <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"d\"><math alttext=\"d\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>d</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>, and the spool spins but does not roll across the table. If the string is pulled with a force of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2 F\"><math alttext=\"2 F\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>F</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>, which of the directions indicated,